&lt;p>If you’re learning Python and find terms like &lt;code>async&lt;/code>, &lt;code>await&lt;/code>, and &lt;code>concurrent tasks&lt;/code> confusing — you’re not alone! This tutorial explains how to write Python code that runs &lt;strong>multiple tasks simultaneously&lt;/strong>, such as reading data from the internet, analyzing logs, and fetching records from a remote server.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Navigating Python Ecosystem</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/dsblog/navigating-python-ecosystem/</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/dsblog/navigating-python-ecosystem/</guid><description>&lt;p>
