&lt;p>Python was created by &lt;strong>Guido van Rossum&lt;/strong> and was first released in 1991. Its design philosophy emphasizes code readability, and its syntax allows programmers to express concepts in fewer lines of code compared to other languages like C++ or Java. Significant milestones in Python’s development include:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Exploring Python Package Manager</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/dsblog/exploring-python-package-manager/</link><pubDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/dsblog/exploring-python-package-manager/</guid><description>&lt;p>
